         <abstract>
            <p>R. E. Crandall has conjectured that for any odd integer &lt;latex&gt;$q &gt; 3$&lt;/latex&gt;, there is a positive integer m whose orbit in the "qx + 1 problem" does not contain 1. We show that this is true for almost all odd numbers q, in the sense of asymptotic density.</p>
          </abstract>
